For this led you will need your 15 5mm leds, lots of wires, your switch, and a breadboard rail and a 220 resistor.
You will send a 5v to the middle switch pin and make it flip the power on and off and then take on side of the 3 pin to your 'hot' power rail
The 220 resistor then comes into play inside the 5v 'hot' rail before the led wires you wire off and adter the main power in
Then each led gets its own jumper into the 5v rail and the gnd into the other rail and then wire the gnd rail to the uno's gnd pin
